Welcome to A Java Tutor!!

Java Install:

Some PCs might have Java already installed. To check whether you have Java installed or not, Put the bellowed command code into a terminal: (powershell,command Prompt)

C:\Users\Your Name>java -version

If Java is installed, you will see something like this (depending on version): java version "18" 2022-03-22 Java(TM) SE Runtime Environment (build 18+36-2087) Java HotSpot(TM) 64-Bit Server VM (build 18+36-2087, mixed mode, sharing) If not, you can download Java for free at the official website oracle.com.
